"title": "1330: God, the provider",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "1330",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>God supplies the needs of all creation, but gives special care to his own people.</p>\n<h2>God is called ``The LORD who provides''</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen22:13-Gen22:14\">GEN 22:13–22:14</a></strong> <em>The name “Yahweh Yireh” (or “Jehovah Jireh”) is from the verb “to see”, and means “The LORD foresees” or “The LORD will see to it”.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen22:8\">GEN 22:8</a></p>\n<h2>God provides for the needs of all creation</h2>\n<h3>He provides for the earth</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps65:9-Ps65:13\">PSA 65:9–65:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut11:12\">DEU 11:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut11:14-Deut11:15\">DEU 11:14–11:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps68:9\">PSA 68:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps104:10-Ps104:18\">PSA 104:10–104:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps135:7\">PSA 135:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps147:8\">PSA 147:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek34:26-Ezek34:29\">EZK 34:26–34:29</a></p>\n<h3>He provides for the animals</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps145:16\">PSA 145:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job38:41\">JOB 38:41</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps104:27-Ps104:28\">PSA 104:27–104:28</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps147:9\">PSA 147:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt6:26\">MAT 6:26</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke12:24\">LUK 12:24</a></p>\n<h3>He provides for all people</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts14:17\">ACT 14:17</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr29:12\">1CH 29:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps68:5\">PSA 68:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps107:9\">PSA 107:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:45\">MAT 5:45</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts17:28\">ACT 17:28</a></p>\n<h3>He provides for the poor and needy</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps140:12\">PSA 140:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam2:8\">1SA 2:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps35:10\">PSA 35:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps145:13-Ps145:14\">PSA 145:13–145:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps146:7-Ps146:9\">PSA 146:7–146:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa25:4\">ISA 25:4</a></p>\n<h2>Special instances of God's practical provision</h2>\n<p>Food and water in the wilderness:\n <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod16:13-Exod16:18\">EXO 16:13–16:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod17:3-Exod17:6\">EXO 17:3–17:6</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num11:4-Num11:9\">NUM 11:4–11:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num11:31-Num11:32\">NUM 11:31–11:32</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs17:6\">1KI 17:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs17:16\">1KI 17:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs19:5-1Kgs19:8\">1KI 19:5–19:8</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs4:42-2Kgs4:44\">2KI 4:42–4:44</a> <em>Elisha feeds 100 men from 20 barley loaves</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt14:15-Matt14:21\">MAT 14:15–14:21</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark6:35-Mark6:44\">MRK 6:35–6:44</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:12-Luke9:17\">LUK 9:12–9:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John6:5-John6:13\">JHN 6:5–6:13</a> <em>Jesus Christ feeds 5,000</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt15:32-Matt15:38\">MAT 15:32–15:38</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark8:1-Mark8:9\">MRK 8:1–8:9</a> <em>Jesus Christ feeds 4,000</em></p>\n<h2>God's special provision for his own people</h2>\n<h3>He provides for their practical needs</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil4:19\">PHP 4:19</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut2:7\">DEU 2:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps68:10\">PSA 68:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps111:5\">PSA 111:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt6:25-Matt6:33\">MAT 6:25–6:33</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke12:22-Luke12:31\">LUK 12:22–12:31</a></p>\n<h3>He provides for their protection</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps5:12\">PSA 5:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen28:15\">GEN 28:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut33:27\">DEU 33:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam2:9\">1SA 2:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps91:9-Ps91:13\">PSA 91:9–91:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps121:3-Ps121:8\">PSA 121:3–121:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa46:4\">ISA 46:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil4:7\">PHP 4:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet1:5\">1PE 1:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jude1:24\">JUD 1:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev3:10\">REV 3:10</a></p>\n<h3>He provides for their every need</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet1:3\">2PE 1:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor3:21-1Cor3:23\">1CO 3:21–3:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col2:10\">COL 2:10</a></p>\n<h3>Examples of God's provision for his people</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam7:10\">2SA 7:10</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr17:9\">1CH 17:9</a> <em>security in the promised land</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa61:3\">ISA 61:3</a> <em>consolation in grief</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer33:6-Jer33:9\">JER 33:6–33:9</a> <em>restoration from captivity</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor10:13\">1CO 10:13</a> <em>a way of escape from temptation</em></p>\n<h2>Implications of God's providential care</h2>\n<h3>Freedom from worry</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt6:31-Matt6:33\">MAT 6:31–6:33</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke12:29-Luke12:31\">LUK 12:29–12:31</a></p>\n<h3>Generosity</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke6:38\">LUK 6:38</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr29:14\">1CH 29:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor9:6-2Cor9:11\">2CO 9:6–9:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil4:18\">PHP 4:18</a></p>\n<h3>Faithfulness</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom2:4\">ROM 2:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa5:1-Isa5:7\">ISA 5:1–5:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos10:1-Hos10:2\">HOS 10:1–10:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos11:1-Hos11:4\">HOS 11:1–11:4</a></p>",
